>>
>> PM confirms Cry_RMIPO_JAT_NEW is not identical to Cry_RMI_PO_ALL — 
>> the JAT format was customised for that customer. PM recommends 
>> adopting the JAT format as the SPINRISE standard because it contains 
>> all required data fields.
>>
>> *My decision:* adopt Cry_RMIPO_JAT_NEW as the SPINRISE standard print 
>> template base, subject to one condition — any JAT-specific branding, 
>> customer name reference, or header element must be replaced with 
>> configurable division-level details from pp_divmas before it is 
>> treated as the universal template. Sasi, update FSD Section 7 to 
>> record: Cry_RMIPO_JAT_NEW is the SPINRISE print template base. 
>> JAT-specific elements to be generalised. FastReports migration to 
>> proceed from this template. Cry_RMI_PO_ALL is retired.
>>
>>
>> *IST-10 — With-Sample mode: Default revised*
>>
>> Nine customer sites confirmed as using wosample=Y: SCM group (5 
>> mills), Skycotex, SLVSM, Poongodhai Spinning, SRG. Given that this is 
>> the majority of major sites, the SPINRISE default for wosample should 
>> be Y, not N as I stated earlier.*I am revising that decision based on 
>> this customer data. *Sasi, update FSD Section 11 accordingly: 
>> wosample SPINRISE default = Y.
>>
>>
>> *On your closing note — an important architectural clarification*
>>
>> You have noted: 'We are using the same customer database; therefore, 
>> setting default flag values separately during implementation is not 
>> required.'
>>
>> Saravanan, this note reflects the current VB6 world where existing 
>> customers continue using their existing database. SPINRISE is not 
>> that. SPINRISE is a new web platform. Here is why default values matter:
>>
>> First, when we onboard a brand new customer who has never used 
>> Kalsofte before, they start with a blank SPINRISE installation. Every 
>> RM_PARAM flag must have a sensible default on day one. Without 
>> documented defaults, onboarding becomes ad hoc guesswork.
>>
>> Second, when we run UAT and testing for SPINRISE, the test 
>> environment starts from a clean database, not a copy of a customer's 
>> live data. The defaults are what the testing team uses to configure 
>> the test environment correctly.
>>
>> Third, when we eventually migrate an existing customer from VB6 to 
>> SPINRISE web, there will be a data migration script. That script must 
>> know which flags to set and at what values for each customer. The 
>> customer-wise breakdown you have provided in IST-1 is exactly the 
>> input for that migration script.
>>
>> The default flag values documentation is not about the current 
>> database. It is about SPINRISE as a product that will be deployed 
>> fresh for new customers and cleanly for existing ones. Please keep 
>> this in mind for all future IST responses across all modules.
>>
>>
