        <meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
          content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
        <p>Dear Saravanan,<br>
          <br>
          Thank you. This is a significant improvement over the first
          round and several long-standing items are now resolved. Let me
          confirm what is accepted, flag two contradictions that need
          clarification, and address your closing note directly.<br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-1 — RM_PARAM flags: Accepted and confirmed</b><br>
          <br>
          This is exactly what was needed. All 8 flags now have customer
          usage context and recommended defaults. <b>Sasi, please
            update FSD Section 11 with the following confirmed values:</b><br>
          <br>
          SuppLotNoReqArrival — used by most customers, mandatory.
          SPINRISE default: Y.<br>
          CentralizedOrder — Pallavaa only (group import PO,
          multi-division arrivals). SPINRISE default: N.<br>
          SeasoncalcReq — not used by any major customers. SPINRISE
          default: N.<br>
          MasterEntryFlg — Pallavaa only (Rate Master entry). SPINRISE
          default: N.<br>
          PO_Approval — at least 1 level mandatory for all customers.
          SPINRISE default: Y.<br>
          ADDTAXREQUIRED — not used by any customer. SPINRISE default:
          N.<br>
          ftamt — not used by any customer. SPINRISE default: N.<br>
          <br>
          One flag requires a CEO decision before Sasi can update the
          FSD. PRBased: Saravanan says SPINRISE default should be N
          because only Pallavaa currently uses PR-based entry. However,
          FSD Section 11 currently documents PRBased default as Y. This
          matters because PRBased=Y makes HSN code and Tax Code
          mandatory on every variety line. PRBased=N removes those
          mandatory checks entirely. For a spinning mill ERP with GST
          compliance built in, PRBased=Y is the safer and more correct
          default for all new customers. My decision: SPINRISE default
          for PRBased = Y. Saravanan, please confirm whether Pallavaa's
          usage is the norm that should be the standard, or the
          exception, because this default will apply to every new
          customer we onboard on SPINRISE.<br>
          <br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-2 — Approval workflow: Substantially resolved, one gap</b><br>
          <br>
          The customer breakdown is now clear. Pallavaa is the only
          customer running 3-level approval. Poongodhai Spinning uses 1
          level. SKS uses 1 level via EDP. Most others have
          PO_Approval=N. Sasi, document this in FSD Section 11 as the
          customer variation for PO_Approval.<br>
          <br>
          The one remaining gap: the web-based approval screen is
          confirmed to exist but its name or URL has not been provided.
          Saravanan, please give the URL path or module name of the web
          approval screen currently used for PO approvals. This goes
          into FSD Section 10 as a Related Screen. It is the one item
          standing between this question and full closure.<br>
          <br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-9 — Crystal report: Decision taken</b><br>
          <br>
          PM confirms Cry_RMIPO_JAT_NEW is not identical to
          Cry_RMI_PO_ALL — the JAT format was customised for that
          customer. PM recommends adopting the JAT format as the
          SPINRISE standard because it contains all required data
          fields.<br>
          <br>
          <b>My decision:</b> adopt Cry_RMIPO_JAT_NEW as the SPINRISE
          standard print template base, subject to one condition — any
          JAT-specific branding, customer name reference, or header
          element must be replaced with configurable division-level
          details from pp_divmas before it is treated as the universal
          template. Sasi, update FSD Section 7 to record:
          Cry_RMIPO_JAT_NEW is the SPINRISE print template base.
          JAT-specific elements to be generalised. FastReports migration
          to proceed from this template. Cry_RMI_PO_ALL is retired.<br>
          <br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-10 — With-Sample mode: Default revised</b><br>
          <br>
          Nine customer sites confirmed as using wosample=Y: SCM group
          (5 mills), Skycotex, SLVSM, Poongodhai Spinning, SRG. Given
          that this is the majority of major sites, the SPINRISE default
          for wosample should be Y, not N as I stated earlier.<b> I am
            revising that decision based on this customer data. </b>Sasi,
          update FSD Section 11 accordingly: wosample SPINRISE default =
          Y.<br>
          <br>
          <br>
          <b>On your closing note — an important architectural
            clarification</b><br>
          <br>
          You have noted: 'We are using the same customer database;
          therefore, setting default flag values separately during
          implementation is not required.'<br>
          <br>
          Saravanan, this note reflects the current VB6 world where
          existing customers continue using their existing database.
          SPINRISE is not that. SPINRISE is a new web platform. Here is
          why default values matter:<br>
          <br>
          First, when we onboard a brand new customer who has never used
          Kalsofte before, they start with a blank SPINRISE
          installation. Every RM_PARAM flag must have a sensible default
          on day one. Without documented defaults, onboarding becomes ad
          hoc guesswork.<br>
          <br>
          Second, when we run UAT and testing for SPINRISE, the test
          environment starts from a clean database, not a copy of a
          customer's live data. The defaults are what the testing team
          uses to configure the test environment correctly.<br>
          <br>
          Third, when we eventually migrate an existing customer from
          VB6 to SPINRISE web, there will be a data migration script.
          That script must know which flags to set and at what values
          for each customer. The customer-wise breakdown you have
          provided in IST-1 is exactly the input for that migration
          script.<br>
          <br>
          The default flag values documentation is not about the current
          database. It is about SPINRISE as a product that will be
