                  (PR balance without UPDLOCK), and CD-4 (RM_DELSCHED
                  without primary key) are important architectural
                  defects that the SPINRISE development team must
                  address. CD-7 (DelReason not written to DB) is
                  correctly flagged as requiring IST confirmation before
                  the fix can be specified.<br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <font size="4"><b>On the PM's feedback — what needs
                      correction before Sasi acts</b></font><br>
                  <br>
                  Saravanan, I want to clarify several points in your
                  feedback before Sasi revises the document.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>First, on tooling:</b> your feedback is marked as
                  ChatGPT feedback. The SPINRISE FSD review process uses
                  Claude AI throughout — for documentation, analysis,
                  and review at every level of the review chain. Please
                  ensure that your IST reviews going forward are
                  conducted using Claude AI, consistent with the rest of
                  the team. This applies to the PM level as well.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>Second, some of your Must Fix items are already in
                    the document:</b><br>
                  <br>
                  The PO number generation race condition is already
                  documented as CD-2 in Section 5.4 and Section 12.1,
                  with the correct SPINRISE fix (locked sequence table
                  with UPDLOCK) already specified. <b>This does not
                    need to be added — it is there.</b><br>
                  <br>
                  The Delete Reason storage question is already in the
                  document as CD-7 in Section 5.10 and as IST-8 in
                  Section 13, both marked as pending IST confirmation.
                  The developer has correctly flagged that the code
                  captures the value but no DB write is observable.
                  IST-8 is your question to answer as the M02 IST member
                  — not something for Sasi to add a note about.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>Third, two of your Important Improvement items are
                    also already in the document:<br>
                  </b><br>
                  With-Sample mode is fully documented in Section 5.8,
                  including the wosample flag, both modes (With-Sample
                  vs Rate-Master), and the difference in GST auto-fill
                  behaviour between the two. Please read Section 5.8.<br>
                  <br>
                  The Season field difference between Add and Modify is
                  documented in Section 5.9 and in Section 3's field
                  rules table. This is already done.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>Fourth, HV-17 and HV-18 are not duplicate
                    validations. </b>They are mirror-image checks —
                  HV-17 fires on LostFocus of the From field (From must
                  be less than or equal to To), and HV-18 fires on
                  LostFocus of the To field (To must be greater than or
                  equal to From). Both are needed at their respective
                  field events and merging them would reduce validation
                  coverage, not improve it.<br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <font size="4"><b>What genuinely needs to be done
                      before this FSD can proceed</b></font><br>
                  <br>
                  <b>For Sasi — two additions required:</b><br>
                  <br>
                  <b>First:</b> The PR-to-PO conversion workflow is
                  missing from Section 5. The document references the PR
                  indent grid (FpSpdInd), the hidden PR linkage fields
                  (iprno, prdate, prsno) in the line items grid, and the
                  SP_PRToPO_RMI and SP_PRToPO_RMIFilter stored
                  procedures — but the business workflow itself is not
                  documented. How does the user load pending PR lines
                  into this screen? What does the PR indent grid show?
                  How does the system match PRs to the PO being created?
                  How does the PR balance reduce after PO save? This is
                  the primary workflow for this screen in daily use and
                  it must be in Section 5. Please add this as Section
                  5.11 — PR to PO Conversion Workflow.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>Second:</b> The CD-1 weignment fix needs to be more
                  specific. Section 12.1 CD-1 says the SPINRISE fix is
                  'save Combo4 selected value to RM_CONT.weignment' —
                  but the form has multiple Combo controls. Which Combo4
                  specifically? Please confirm the correct combo control
                  that drives the weighment selection and update the
                  SPINRISE action accordingly.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>For Sasi — one item requiring SP code submission:</b><br>
                  <br>
                  SP_PRToPO_RMI and SP_PRToPO_RMIFilter are listed in
                  the Document Identity table but their internal logic
                  is not analysed in Section 8. These two SPs handle the
                  PR-to-PO conversion, which is the most
                  business-critical workflow in this screen. Please
                  obtain both SP codes from SQL Server Management Studio
                  and submit them to Claude using Follow-up Prompt B
                  from the v2 guide. The analysis output belongs in
                  Section 8.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>For Saravanan — your IST responsibilities:</b><br>
                  <br>
                  As the IST member for M02, Section 13 is yours to
                  complete. All 10 IST questions are currently showing
                  PENDING. The two critical ones that must be answered
                  before this FSD can move to TL-IST review are IST-8
                  (DelReason: is the DelReasonCode written to
                  RM_Trans_Log.DelReason or a separate table? — this
                  resolves CD-7) and IST-9 (Cry_RMIPO_JAT_NEW vs
                  Cry_RMI_PO_ALL: what changed in the Crystal report
                  layout and data? — this unblocks the FastReports
                  migration scope for M02). <b>Please complete your IST
                    review of Section 13 and respond to Sasi directly so
                    the document can be updated.<br>
                  </b><br>
                  <b>The PM's additions that are genuinely valid and can
                    be included by Sasi:<br>
                  </b><br>
                  A brief PR-based vs Direct PO flow distinction in
                  Section 1 or 5 (which Sasi is already adding in
                  Section 5.11 above). Three technical additions to
                  Section 12 are reasonable: an API endpoint list
                  (Create, Update, Delete, List PO), an explicit
                  single-transaction scope statement for the Save
                  sequence, and a concurrency handling note covering PO
                  numbering and PR balance. An Assumptions section and
                  an Out of Scope section can be added as a Section 0 or
                  appended after Section 14.<br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <font size="4"><b>Overall</b></font><br>
                  <br>
                  <b>Sasi, do not act on the PM's full list as written.</b>
                  The specific actions for you are: add Section 5.11 for
                  the PR-to-PO conversion workflow, clarify the Combo4
                  reference in CD-1, obtain and submit the two SP codes
                  to Claude, and add the three technical additions to
                  Section 12 that are genuinely missing. Wait for
                  Saravanan's IST responses on IST-8 and IST-9 before
                  resubmitting.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>Saravanan</b>, please complete your IST review of
                  Section 13 by today. IST-8 and IST-9 in particular are
                  blocking items.<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>This FSD is close to ready. The core work is
                    excellent.</b><br>
                  <br>
                  Regards,<br>
                  T. Mani<br>
